# AG Grid feature research — required before implementation

This repo builds Tabular (`packages/core`), a canvas-first grid whose features,
API surface, theme, and look-and-feel must match AG Grid v35+ (the reference
app `apps/agref` pins the installed version — check it, it may be v36+).

Before implementing, changing, or verifying ANY grid feature, complete this
research phase first. Do not write feature code before it is done.

## 1. Gather the authoritative API surface

- Read the installed type definitions (most authoritative, exact version):
  - `node_modules/ag-grid-community/dist/types/src/entities/gridOptions.d.ts`
  - `node_modules/ag-grid-community/dist/types/src/entities/colDef.d.ts`
  - `node_modules/ag-grid-community/dist/types/src/api/gridApi.d.ts`
  - `node_modules/ag-grid-community/dist/types/src/events.d.ts`
  - Feature interfaces under `node_modules/ag-grid-community/dist/types/src/interfaces/`
- Fetch the current AG Grid docs page(s) for the feature
  (https://www.ag-grid.com/react-data-grid/<feature>/) for behavior, nuances,
  defaults, deprecations, and interactions with other features. Also check
  `agref.txt` in the repo root.

## 2. Produce a feature checklist before coding

Enumerate, explicitly:

- All grid options + col-def options for the feature (names, types, defaults)
- All GridApi methods and their exact signatures
- All events (including start/end pairs, e.g. `pasteStart`/`pasteEnd`)
- Callback/processor hooks (e.g. `processCellFromClipboard`)
- Behavioral nuances: edge cases, precedence, what happens on empty/filtered
  data, keyboard interactions, deprecated options to avoid
- UI/UX details: labels, layout, icons, overlays wording, status bar text

## 3. Implement and verify

- Match AG names and semantics exactly in `packages/core/src/types.ts` unless
  physically impossible in a canvas grid; document intentional deviations.
- Never introduce invented option names when an AG equivalent exists
  (past example: a custom `treeDataKeyField` had to be replaced by AG's
  `autoGroupColumnDef.field`).
- Add/extend a matching page in `apps/agref` and verify side by side in the
  browser (same seeded data), comparing behavior, wording, and visuals — not
  just compilation.
